The paper discusses a method for reducing the volume of information that needs to be transmitted in moving big data, without loss of information, from one place to another, or in lossless communications via the internet. This is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of the SP theory of intelligence and its realisation in the SP computer model, which involves unsupervised learning and encoding/decoding of data. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for lossless transmission of data, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
